# Socket Handlers

Socket.IO server-side handlers for AI chat, DM, cross-tab sync, and gamification notifications.

**Reference:** `server/src/sockets/index.ts`

## Socket Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart TB
  C1[Tab 1] --> S[Socket.IO Server]
  C2[Tab 2] --> S
  C3[Tab 3] --> S
  S --> R[user:{userId} Room]
  C1 -. joins .-> R
  C2 -. joins .-> R
  C3 -. joins .-> R
  S --> A[AI Service]
  S --> D[DM Service]
  S --> Q[Quest Service]
  S --> M[Mood Service]
```

## Authentication Middleware

```typescript
io.use(async (socket, next) => {
  const token = socket.handshake.auth.token || socket.handshake.headers.authorization;
  const decoded = jwt.verify(token, process.env.JWT_SECRET);
  // Cache-aside: Redis (10min TTL) → DB fallback
  const user = await cache.get(`user:auth:${decoded.userId}`);
  socket.userId = user.id;
  next();
});
```

## Connection Setup

On connect, each socket joins `user:{userId}` room for cross-tab sync across all tabs/devices.

## Handler: `message:send`

AI chat message processing with deduplication via Redis setNX.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
  participant T as Tab (Socket)
  participant S as Socket Server
  participant R as Redis (dedup)
  participant AI as AI Service
  participant DB as Database

  T->>S: message:send { characterId, content, clientId }
  S->>S: Rate limit check (10/10s)
  S->>S: Input validation (trim, length ≤ 2000)
  S->>R: setNX dedup:{userId}:{clientId}
  R-->>S: isNew = false → drop duplicate
  S->>T: emit character:typing (to all tabs in room)
  S->>AI: chatService.sendMessage()
  AI->>AI: Generate AI response + emotion + facts
  AI->>DB: Save user message + AI response
  AI->>DB: Update affection, mood, level
  AI-->>S: { userMessage, aiMessage, emotion, affectionChange, ... }
  S->>T: emit message:receive (user msg + clientId, isOwn: true)
  S->>S: Typing delay: min(4000, max(1500, length * 25))
  S->>T: emit message:receive (AI response)
  S->>T: emit character:affection_change (if changed)
  S->>T: emit quest:completed (if any)
  S->>T: emit milestone:unlocked (if any)
```

**Response broadcasts (all to `user:{userId}` room):**

| Event | Condition |
|---|---|
| `message:receive` (user) | Always — echo with `isOwn: true, clientId` |
| `character:typing` | Always — before AI processing |
| `message:receive` (AI) | After typing delay |
| `character:mood_change` | If mood changed |
| `character:affection_change` | If affection changed (includes level/relationship data) |
| `quest:completed` | If quests completed |
| `milestone:unlocked` | If milestones unlocked |

**Typing delay:** `1000 + Math.random() * 2000` (1-3s) before AI response, proportional to content length.

## Handler: `dm:send`

User-to-user messaging for 1-on-1 and group chats (3-50 members).

```typescript
socket.on('dm:send', async ({ conversationId, content, clientId }) => {
  // Rate limit: 20/60s
  // Idempotency: dedup_dm:{userId}:{clientId} via setNX
  const message = await dmService.sendMessage(userId, conversationId, content);

  // Broadcast to all conversation members
  members.forEach(m => io.to(`user:${m.userId}`).emit('dm:receive', message));
});
```

**Member caching:** Conversation members cached for 5 minutes to avoid DB query on every message.

## Handler: `dm:typing`

```typescript
socket.on('dm:typing', async ({ conversationId }) => {
  // Rate limit: 30/60s
  // Broadcast to other members (exclude current user)
  members.filter(m => m.userId !== userId).forEach(m => {
    io.to(`user:${m.userId}`).emit('dm:typing', { conversationId, userId });
  });
});
```

## Handler: `dm:read`

```typescript
socket.on('dm:read', async ({ conversationId }) => {
  await dmService.markRead(userId, conversationId);
});
```

## Handler: `sync:request` / `sync:response`

Cross-tab state synchronization:

```
Tab A (new)           Server              Tab B (existing)
   |                     |                      |
   |-- sync:request ---->|                      |
   |                     |-- sync:state_request->|
   |                     |<-- sync:response -----|
   |                     |  { messages, typing } |
   |<-- sync:state_receive                      |
   |  { messages, typing }                      |
```

## Handler: `character:mood_check`

```typescript
socket.on('character:mood_check', async ({ characterId }) => {
  const mood = await moodService.getCurrentMood(characterId);
  io.to(userRoom).emit('character:mood_update', { characterId, ...mood });
});
```

## Proactive Notification Check

On every connection, checks for proactive AI notifications (debounced per user, once per 5 minutes):

```typescript
// Debounce: proactive_notif:{userId} → 300s TTL
// Character list cached: user:{userId}:characters:list → 300s TTL
const result = await proactiveNotificationService.checkAndSendNotification(characterId);
if (result.shouldSend) {
  io.to(userRoom).emit('notification:proactive', {
    characterId, characterName, type, message, sourceSocketId,
  });
}
```

## Rate Limiting Summary

| Event Type | Max Requests | Window | Config Key |
|---|---|---|---|
| `message:send` | 10 | 10s | `SOCKET_MESSAGE_SEND` |
| `dm:send` | 20 | 60s | `SOCKET_DM_SEND` |
| `dm:typing` | 30 | 60s | `SOCKET_TYPING` |

Implementation: In-memory `Map<string, { count, resetAt }>` with per-user-per-event keys.

